rComments: Very good lectures and interesting assignments, but grading criteria is often unclear, so make sure to ask lots of questions about them in class. For this class there is also a 2 month long group project, so if you don't like those, don't take this class.
Great class. Very passionate about what she does

She is the best prof ive ever had at the university of ottawa. She is clearly passionate about what she's teaches and is clear with her instructions. As long as you pay attention and do your work you'll get a good grade.

Good prof but not amazing. Very interesting class but the tasks seemed unclear at times and she didn't always have much patience. So many useless quizzes we had to complete to get access to any tests which I found odd.

The teacher is really understanding. During the session, the teacher takes time to make qualitiy videos and powerpoints for the students and adds additional infos if u don't understand. She is available to answer the students questions and is very dedicated to her students. Would take that course again for sure!!!

Prof Dagher was a really good. She was always clear in her her lectures and in her instructions. We had 4 papers throughout the whole course (including the final). She's very nice and understanding. Get ready to put in the work tho. This is not an easy A. You actually have to dedicate a bit of time for this course. I still recommend this course!

Her lectures are always very interesting. She is very direct and approachable. This won't sound good but it is: She made me realize DVM wasn't for me and I am very grateful to have taken this class with her to get an early wake-up call. I definitely recommend taking her classes!

Prof Dagher is very caring and understanding. The instructions for assignments were always vague. No midterms, just papers/weekly assignments. Completely based off your own critical thinking rather than research based work. No final exam, just a group project. Lectures were recorded and posted, so no live class.

I loved Professor Ruby. Her class was always interesting and she was very passionate about what she was talking about. Her tests mainly focus of critical thinking but if you listen in class and review her powerpoints you'll do just fine.

Professor Dagher offers a fresh new perspective to development which makes her lectures interesting. Her tangents are really capturing (in my opinion) and I respect her for encouraging critical thinking. The entire course is a big group project and if you take her advice and feedback you'll do fine. Expectations relatively unclear so ask questions.
Incredibly condescending, often goes on ideological tangents and fails to finish the lecture. Tough marker, but generally provides good feedback.

Ruby is a great professor. Almost all of your marks for the class will come from a group project that is the development of an international development project. While she is a tough marker for the first few group assignments, if you heed her feedback you will do very well in the final presentation. Only complaint is that she is a huge pessimist.

Although her slides can be wordy and lectures hard to follow, you can tell she is really passionate about the subject and encourages class participation. Exams are straight forward as long as you came to class

The greatest prof I've ever had. I started the course off with a 45%, I spoke to her and she was very understanding for my situation. she showed me that she believed in me and I was so motivated in her class. Study her powerpoints and you'll get an A.

A wonderful professor and my beliefs completely changed about the world and Canada. Papers and assignements were graded quite late so keep that in mind. Overall I would take any classes Dagher teaches!

Knowledgeable and passionate about her stuff. Her lectures are pretty disorganized and her ability to convey information is pretty lacking. Her grading criteria are super unclear, took forever to give back grades. Language is also a barrier as french is not her mother tongue. Tough grader for unclear reasons. Would not take again.

The best prof I have had at uOttawa. So passionate and extremely knowledgeable - she always applies her practical experience to lectures. Doesn't preach dogma but emphasizes critical analysis and making your own decisions based on all the info. Truly recommend taking at least one class with her if you're in dvm!

Ruby is very knowledgeable on the material that she covers in class, however, there are many things wrong with the way she teaches. She can be very condescending towards her students, doesn't have a clear outline of what she wants from projects and the amount of time spent on an assignment is not reflected in the amount it is worth.
Patronizing and no one understood what she wanted from the group projects. Level of work does NOT reflect the percentage weight of the assignment.

She does not provide outlines and gets frustrated when you ask for clarification on assignment requirements. Expects students to figure out what she wants from assignments without giving much instruction. Can be condescending when students don't understand something.
She doesn't answer her emails and takes a long time to grade her paper also really sloppy with her work. Would not recommend her

Ruby is an amazing professor. She's very educated in Policy through using her own personal experience at GAC. I admire how she is always able to relate course content back to current day issues. She really cares for her students and is always available to help regardless of her busy schedule. Highly recommend taking a class with Ruby!

She is very insightful in the field of int' l development, especially in policy and practice because of her diplomatic background. She provides many realistic examples and expectations about working in the field. She knows how the broken and corrupt system functions. Regardless, she is very inspiring! She's a game changer, so I highly recommend her

This is the best prof of the faculty of International DVM. Make sure you take her class at least one time  so you can see the program differently. French or english, she inspires students and is very good at teaching. She is a good marker and makes sure you always understand what she covers in class. Have fun with Ruby :)
Best prof of my undergrad..... Let her inspire you.

Prof Dagher is one of the best profs if not THE BEST simply because she cares about students really learning and practicing to analyse complex situations and resolving it after considering every perspectives (sth rare). She has experience in the field beside her studies. Very nice and kind, easy-going, open-minded and down-to-earth teacher.
Amazing teacher! Would definitely take any class with her as the professor. She is passionate and knowledgable. One of the best classes I have taken in university.

She is undoubtedly one if the best teacher I ever had. She think outside the box and her classes and the reflexions that she brings are really thought-provoking. She respects the student's opinion and always pushes you to think further. She's really engaged with her students and really wants you to succeed! You must take a class with her!!!

An incredible prof, definitely deserves more recognition than she gets. Her content knowledge is incredible, and combined with her critical analysis (which she WILL expect you to have mastered once the course is done) is always on point. It's tough, but oh so worth it. Recommend always.
I want to be her when I grow up #rolemodel

Prof. Dagher is one of the best profs I've ever had for several reasons. She is very engaging and focuses on critical analysis  of the development process. She wants you to learn and expand your mind to see both sides of every story. Her experience in the field adds immersion into her teaching style. She is a gem of a prof and I'd recommend her.
BEST PROF of uOttawa!!!

Professor Dagher changed the entire way I think and I cannot be more grateful! She offers a different approach with lots of experience, using every opportunity to push your ability to think critically. Best professor I have had hands down! She does not require you to memorize, but rather to engage and think about the material and actually learn!A++

This prof does her best to enrich the student's learning experience. However her past experience with the development process clouds her judgment to educate rather than critique neoliberal policies. Failure to agree with her ideology results in harder grading. You'll get a higher mark if you just go with her opinion rather than you're own.

Can't recommend this prof enough! She's just getting started out but I hope that the University gives her more classes to teach.  She's passionate about development and has lots of relevant experience.  She's critical of the current development system, but gives well rounded information and facts. I never missed her class and hope to see her again!
